and N-palmitoyl-Cer, respectively. Quantitation of PE and PS was performed by neutral loss scanning, selecting for a neutral loss of 141 Da or 185 Da (positive ion mode), respectively, with a collision energy of 20 eV. pl-PE quantitation was performed by precursor ion scanning for fragment ion m z 196 Da (negative ion mode; collision energy of 40 eV). Unsaturated PE and PS standards were synthesized and purified via HPLC as described (36). Quantitative analyses were performed as described (13, 37). Phosphate determination was performed according to Rouser (38).
